original_title: Bronx: Castle Hill Avenue - Norton Avenue
text:
Castle Hill Avenue, east side, north of Norton Avenue, showing part of the house and the estate of John Screven stretching out toward Westchester Creek and the East River. Screven inherited the property from his father-in-law Gouverneur Morris Wilkins.

Between 1900 and 1913

original_title: Bronx: Castle Hill Avenue - Norton Avenue
text:
Castle Hill Ave., east side, north of Norton Ave., showing the John Screven (also spelled Screvin) Mansion. It originally belonged to Gouverneur Morris Wilkins and later to his son-in-law John Screven, after whom the area is familiarly known as Screven's Point.

Between 1900 and 1913.
